"{\"uid\": \"koaa.com-news-covering-colorado-2024-paris-olympic-medal-tracker\", \"text\": \"The Paris Olympics have officially kicked off! You can keep up with all of your Olympics content here on KOAA-TV.  Team USA was off to a strong start to the games for the first weekend, bringing in 12 medals throughout the opening weekend of the games.  Those medals all have ties to Olympic City USA as according to the city those medals were won by athletes who have worked and trained in Olympic City USA.    Below you can see which sports Team USA has won medals in and which athletes competed to bring the medals home.  So far, Team USA has dominated in swimming bringing home 28 medals. Of these, eight are gold, 13 are silver, and seven are bronze.  Katie Ledecky - Women's 800M Freestyle  Bobby Finke - Gold, Men's 1500M Freestyle  Katie Ledecky - Gold, Women's 1500M Freestyle  Kate Douglass - Gold, Women's 200M Breaststroke  Torri Huske - Gold, Women's 100 M Butterfly  Jack Alexy, Chris Guiliano, Hunter Armstrong, and Caeleb Dressel - Gold, Men's 4X100M Freestyle Relay  Regan Smith, Lilly King, Gretchen Walsh and Torri Huske - Gold, Women's 4X100 Medley Relay  Ryan Murphy, Gretchen Walsh, Nic Fink, and Torri Huske - Gold, Mixed 4X100 Medley Relay  Torri Huske - Silver, Women's 100M Freestyle  Bobby Finke - Silver, Men's 800M Freestyle  Regan Smith - Silver, Women's 100M Backstroke  Regan Smith - Silver, Women's 200M Backstroke  Nic Fink - Silver,  Men's 100M Breastroke  Gretchen Walsh - Silver,  Women's 100M Butterfly  Regan Smith - Silver, Women's 200M Butterfly  Kate Douglass - Silver, Women's 200M IM  Katie Grimes - Silver,  Women's 400M IM  Simone Manuel, Kate Douglass, Gretchen Walsh, and Torri Huske - Silver, Women's 4X100M Freestyle Relay  Luke Hobson, Carson Foster, Drew Kibler and Kieran Smith - Silver, Men's 4X200M Freestyle Relay  Katie Ledecky, Paige Madden, Claire Weinstein and Erin Gemmell - Silver, Women's 4X200M Freestyle Relay  Ryan Murphy, Nic Fink, Caeleb Dressel and Hunter Armstrong - Silver, Men's 4X100M Medley Relay  Luke Hobson - Bronze, Men's 200M Freestyle  Katie Ledecky - Bronze,  Women's 400M Freestyle  Paige Madden - Bronze, Women's 800M Freestyle  Ryan Murphy - Bronze, Men's 100M Backstroke  Katharine Berkoff - Bronze, Women's 100M Backstroke  Carson Foster - Bronze, Men's 400M IM  Emma Weyant - Bronze, Women's 400M IM  The fencing competition led to an interesting final in the women's individual foil as it was Team USA's Lauren Scruggs up against Team USA's Lee Kiefer. The two battled it out with Lee Kiefer taking the Gold and Scruggs winding up with the Silver.  Lee Kiefer -  Gold, Women's Individual Foil  Lauren Scruggs, Lee Kiefer, Jacqueline Dubrovich and Maia Weintraub - Gold, Women's Team Foil  Lauren Scruggs - Silver, Women's Individual Foil  Nick Itkin - Bronze, Men's Individual Foil  Skateboarding returns for only the second time on the Olympic stage since its debut in Tokyo in 2020.  In the men's street final two Americans took second and third.  Tom Schaar - Silver, Men's Park  Jagger Eaton - Silver, Men's Street  Nyjah Huston - Bronze, Men's Street  Bam Adebayo, Devin Booker, Stephen Curry, Anthony Davis, Kevin Durant, Anthony Edwards, Joel Embiid, Tyrese Haliburton, Jrue Holiday, LeBron James, Jayson Tatum and Derrick White - Gold, Men's Tournament  Napheesa Collier, Kahleah Copper, Chelsea Gray, Brittney Griner, Sabrina Ionescu, Jewell Loyd, Kelsey Plum, Breanna Stewart, Diana Taurasi, Alyssa Thomas, A'ja Wilson and Jackie Young - Gold, Women's Tournament  Justin Best, Nick Mead, Michael Grady and Liam Corrigan - Gold, Men's Four  Clark Dean, Henry Hollingsworth, Nick Rusher, Christian Tabash, Chris Carlson, Peter Chatain, Evan Olson, Pieter Quinton, Rielly Milne - Bronze, Men's Eight  Sarah Bacon, Kassidy Cook - Silver, Women's Synchronized 3M Springs  Laura Kraut, Karl Cook, McLain Ward - Silver, Team Jumping  Vincent Hancock - Gold, Men's Skeet  Sagen Maddalena - Silver, Women's Smallbore Rifle, 3 Positions  Conner Prince - Silver, Men's Skeet  Austen Smith, Vincent Hancock - Silver, Mixed Team Skeet  Austen Smith - Bronze, Women's Skeet  Brady Ellison - Silver, Men's Individual  Casey Kaufhold, Brady Ellison - Bronze, Mixed Team  In what has been considered a redemption arc for Team USA,  the women's and men's teams both came to Paris with big expectations. Clinching a medal for the first time since 2008, the men's team secured bronze. The women's team came looking to return to the podium and they did, getting revenge and gold after the Tokyo 2020 silver finish.  Simone Biles - Gold, Women's Vault  Simone Biles - Gold, Women's All-Around  Simone Biles, Suni Lee, Jordan Chiles, Jade Carey and Hezly Rivera - Gold, Women's Team Final  Simone Biles - Silver, Women's Floor Exercise  Suni Lee - Bronze, Women's All-Around  Asher Hong, Paul Juda, Brody Malone, Stephen Nedoroscik and Frederick Richard - Bronze, Men's Team Final  Suni Lee - Bronze, Women's Uneven Bars  Jade Carey - Bronze, Women's Vault  Stephen Nedoroscik - Bronze, Men's Pommel Horse  On July 28, Haley Batten's silver medal in mountain biking was the best-ever finish for any American in the event.  Kristen Faulkner - Gold, Women's Road Race  Jennifer Valente - Gold, Track; Women's Omnium  Jennifer Valente, Chlo\\u00e9 Dygert, Kristen Faulkner, and Lily Williams - Gold,Track; Women's Team Pursuit  Haley Batten - Silver, Women's Mountain Bike  Perris Benegas - Silver, Women's BMX Freestyle  Chloe Dygert - Bronze, Women's Time Trial  Women's National Team - Bronze  Ian Barrows, Hans Henken - Bronze, Men's Skiff  Sam Watson - Bronze, Men's Speed  Kristina Teachout - Bronze, Women's 67KG/148LBS  Tyler Abramson, Alex Bowen, Luca Cupido, Hannes Daube, Chase Dodd, Ryder Dodd, Ben Hallock, Drew Holland, Johnny Hooper, Max Irving, Alex Obert, Marko Vavic, Adrian Weinberg, Dylan Woodhead and Quinn Woodhead - Bronze, Men's Tournament  Jordyn Poulter, Avery Skinner, Justine Wong-Orantes, Lauren Carlini, Jordan Larson, Annie Drews, Jordan Thompson, Haleigh Washington, Dana Rettke, Kathryn Plummer, Kelsey Robinson Cook, Chiaka Ogbogu - Silver, Women's Tournament  Matt Anderson, Aaron Russell, Jeff Jendryk, T.J. DeFalco, Micah Christenson, Max Holt, Micah Ma'a, Thomas Jaeschke, Garrett Muagututia, Taylor Averill, David Smith and Erik Shoji- Bronze, Men's Tournament  Olivia Reeves - Gold, Women's 71KG/156LBS  Hampton Morris - Bronze, Men's 61KG/134LBS  Noah Lyles won what looked like a five-way tie in the Men's 100m. Ryan Crouser continued his dominance in Men's Shot Put becoming the only person to be a three-time gold medalist in the event. Sha'Carri Richardson wins silver in her Olympic debut.  Noah Lyles - Gold, Men's 100M  Gabby Thomas - Gold, Women's 200M  Quincy Hall - Gold, Men's 400M  Cole Hocker - Gold, Men's 1500M  Grant Holloway - Gold, Men's 110M Hurdles  Masai Russell - Gold, Women's 110M Hurdles  Rai Benjamin - Gold, Men's 400M Hurdles  Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone - Gold, Women's 400M Hurdles  Tara Davis-Woodhall - Gold, Women's Long Jump  Ryan Crouser - Gold, Men's Shot Put  Valarie Allman - Gold, Women's Discus  Gabby Thomas, Sha'Carri Richardson, Melissa Jefferson and Twanisha Terry - Gold, Women's 4X100M Relay  Rai Benjamin, Christopher Bailey, Bryce Deadmon and Vernon Norwood - Gold, Men's 4X400M Relay  Shamier Little, Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone, Gabby Thomas and Alexis Holmes - Gold, Women's 4X400M Relay  Sha'Carri Richardson - Silver, Women's 100M  Kenny Bednarek - Silver, Men's 200M  Kenneth Rooks - Silver, Men's 3000M Steeplechase  Daniel Roberts - Silver, Men's 110M Hurdles  Anna Cockrell - Silver, Women's 400M Hurdles  Shelby McEwen - Silver, Men's High Jump  Sam Kendricks - Silver, Men's Pole Vault  Katie Moon - Silver, Women's Pole Vault  Joe Kovacs - Silver, Men's Shot Put  Annette Echikunwoke - Silver, Women's Hammer  Vernon Norwood, Shamier Little, Bryce Deadmon, Kaylyn Brown - Silver, Mixed 4x400 Relay  Fred Kerley - Bronze, Men's 100M  Melissa Jefferson - Bronze, Women's 100M  Noah Lyles - Bronze, Men's 200M  Brittany Brown - Bronze, Women's 200M  Yared Nuguse - Bronze, Men's 1500M  Grant Fisher - Bronze, Men's 5,000M  Grant Fisher - Bronze, Men's 10,000M  Jasmine Moore - Bronze, Women's Long Jump  Jasmine Moore - Bronze, Women's Triple Jump  Evy Leibfarth - Bronze,  Women's Canoe Slalom  Cierra Burdick, Dearica Hamby and Rhyne Howard, and Hailey Van Lith - Bronze, Women's Tournament  Omari Jones - Bronze, Men's 71KG/156LBS (Welterweight)  Victor Montalvo - Bronze, Men's Event  Casey Murphy, Alyssa Naeher, Tierna Davidson, Emily Fox, Naomi Girma, Casey Krueger, Jenna Nighswonger, Emily Sonnett, Korbin Albert, Sam Coffey, Lindsey Horan, Rose Lavelle, Crystal Dunn, Trinity Rodman, Jaedyn Shaw, Sophia Smith, Mallory Swanson and Lynn Williams - Gold, Women's Tournament  Caroline Marks - Gold, Women's Event  Anita Alvarez, Daniella Ramirez, Keana Hunter, Audrey Kwon, Jaime Czarkwoski, Ruby Remati, Jacklyn Luu, and Megumi Field - Silver, Team  Sarah Hildebrandt - Gold, Women's Freestyle 50KG/110LBS  Amit Elor - Gold, Women's Freestyle 68KG/149LBS  Spencer Lee - Silver, Men's Freestyle 57KG/125LBS  Kennedy Alexis Blades - Silver, Women's Freestyle 76KG/167LBS  Kyle Dake - Bronze, Men's Freestyle 74KG/163LBS  Aaron Brooks - Bronze, Men's Freestyle 86KG/189LBS  Helen Maroulis - Bronze, Women's Freestyle 57KG/125LBS  Taylor Fritz, Tommy Paul - Bronze, Men's Doubles  ___    A three-year-old goat named Pongo is making the holidays brighter for families in southern Colorado, one bell ring at a time.      ____  Watch KOAA News5 on your time, anytime with our free streaming app available for your Roku, FireTV, AppleTV and Android TV.  Just searchKOAA News5, download and start watching.  Report a typo\"}"